she's done more work before 7:00
in the morning

22:02.121 --> 22:03.656 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
than you expected anyone to.

22:03.689 --> 22:05.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
®MD-BO /JAMES ROSEBUSH, Former
Nancy Reagan
Chief of Staff: That's right.

22:05.491 --> 22:08.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
By the time I got to the office
and went to
the senior staff meeting, she'd
read all the

22:08.227 --> 22:12.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
morning papers, she had seen all
the morning
shows, she had the advanced
copies of the

22:12.231 --> 22:15.868 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
newsweeklies, and she knew
exactly what she
thought.

22:15.901 --> 22:20.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So she was a highly intelligent
woman. I think
that was lost on a lot of
people. They didn't

22:20.406 --> 22:27.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
recognize that. And she was
engaged not only
in her own program and schedule,
but very

22:27.279 --> 22:33.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
observant of what the president
was doing.
And she was a person who,
therefore, was easy

22:33.852 --> 22:38.224 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to work for, because she knew
what she wanted
and she communicated it well.

22:38.257 --> 22:43.929 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And it was obviously an
extraordinary honor
to work for her, to work for
both of them.

22:43.963 --> 22:48.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Michael, what
he's describing
is almost what you would expect
from a chief

22:48.234 --> 22:51.003 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of staff, not necessarily just a
first lady.

22:51.036 --> 22:53.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL BESCHLOSS, Presidential
Historian:
That's what I have always
thought.

22:53.639 --> 22:57.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You might have, for instance,
Hillary Clinton,
who at the beginning of her
husband's administration

22:57.376 --> 23:03.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was given this health care
project, but Nancy
Reagan without any title other
than first

23:03.649 --> 23:08.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lady really was sort of an
