and uncritical
of her husband and also for
acting as his

26:03.695 --> 26:06.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
political partner, especially on
key occasions.

26:06.965 --> 26:11.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nowadays, I think things have
changed enough
that we would celebrate her for
doing most

26:11.603 --> 26:16.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
those things. And it is amazing
to look back
and think that those were two of
the things

26:16.809 --> 26:18.610 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
she caught the most flak for.

26:18.644 --> 26:21.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: James, when
you worked with
her, what did you think her
legacy was going

26:21.513 --> 26:25.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be, vs. now, decades later,
knowing what
she's accomplished?

26:25.417 --> 26:27.152 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAMES ROSEBUSH: Yes, it's
interesting.

26:27.186 --> 26:31.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The whole concept of legacy is
interesting,
